COACH SMITH:  First of all we congratulate Arkansas on a well-played game.  They shot the ball real well, and Corliss Williamson got loose in the second half and hurt us.  I think overall defensively we did a good job, except for Williamson, and Robinson hurt us with the 3 pointer, and the end of the first half.  But the real win was about two minutes and a half when he made that one.  But then you have to hand it to our players that came back and had a great chance to win the game. And I think we all felt that we would, after Jerry made those foul shots, and we didn't get exactly what we wanted there in the last 18 seconds.  But still, anytime Donald has an open look, he has the green light, and he's been very good for us for many years. And it's a s            
          
